Pro Tips:

1.  POJOs do not have to map or match exactly to their corresponding
	SQL tables in a database 
2.	Break points for debugging: best practice to place it on the 
	first line of executable code 
3.	Store MySQL passwords in keychain (for Mac users)
4. 	Switch databases in MySQL by double clicking on database you 	
	want to work with 
	
SQL: Structured Query Language

MySQL
-database technology/application 
-can access via terminal by logging into the MySQL shell 

MySQL Workbench
-GUI for connecting to and managing a MySQL database 

SQL databases 
-relational
-analytical(OLAP)

NoSQL databases
-column-family
-graph
-document
-key-value

Accessing MySQL via the CLI

starting MySQL:
sudo /usr/local/mysql/support-files/mysql.server start 

(will get error if MySQL already running)

alternative to above method: 

sudo launchctl load -F /Library/LaunchDaemons com.oracle.oss.mysql.mysqld.plist 


check version of MySQL:

mysql --version

Accessing column in MySQL table: table_name.column_name

Column Attributes:

PK: primary key
NN: not null
UN: unsigned (only positive integers)
AI: auto increment
G: generated column 
